#### Functional Features Analysis\
\
##### 1.1 User Authentication and Dashboard\
- **Description**: Users register, log in, and access a dashboard to manage video projects and settings.\
- **Key Features**:\
  - Secure registration and login using email/password, with JWT authentication for session management.\
  - Dashboard displays recent videos, scheduled posts, and analytics summaries, with navigation to key sections.\
- **Implementation Details**:\
  - Frontend: React.js or Vue.js for responsive UI, with form components for login/register.\
  - Backend: Node.js (Express) or Python (Django/Flask) handles authentication, storing hashed passwords in MongoDB/PostgreSQL.\
  - Security: HTTPS, input validation to prevent SQL injection/XSS, rate limiting for API abuse.\
- **User Flow**: From the homepage, users click "Register/Login," enter credentials, and are redirected to the Dashboard, displaying a grid of recent videos and analytics (App Flow Document, Stage 1).\
- **Feasibility**: Bubble can handle user authentication and dashboards, aligning with the user's no-code approach, with team support for any complex setups.\
\
##### 1.2 Video Creation\
- **Description**: Users input a topic/prompt to initiate AI-driven video generation.\
- **Key Features**:\
  - Input field for topic/prompt, with language and voice profile selection.\
  - Real-time progress tracking via a status screen, with notifications on completion.\
- **Implementation Details**:\
  - Frontend: Form components for input, dropdowns for language/voice, "Generate Video" button.\
  - Backend: Integrates with OpenAI for script generation, ElevenLabs for voiceover, and Cling AI for video generation via APIs, processed asynchronously with RabbitMQ/Redis Queue.\
  - Video Processing: FFmpeg or AWS Elastic Transcoder for merging, with results stored in S3, URLs in the database.\
- **User Flow**: Users navigate to "Create Video," input a prompt, select options, click "Generate," and see progress on the status screen, redirected to customization on completion (App Flow Document, Stage 3).\
- **Feasibility**: RunwayML's plugin for Bubble handles video generation, with the user's prompting skills aiding configuration, supported by team for backend integrations.\
\
##### 1.3 Customization\
- **Description**: Users personalize generated videos before finalizing.\
- **Key Features**:\
  - Rich text editor for script editing, music library selector, voice profile selector, subtitle editor with style options, live preview.\
- **Implementation Details**:\
  - Frontend: Quill.js for script editing, grid for music selection, dropdowns for voice, subtitle editor with style options, video player for preview.\
  - Backend: APIs save customization data, re-process videos with AI APIs for changes, using FFmpeg for updates.\
- **User Flow**: On the Preview/Customization screen, users edit scripts, select music/voice, add subtitles, preview changes, and save, with real-time updates (App Flow Document, Stage 4).\
- **Feasibility**: Bubble's UI capabilities support customization, with RunwayML handling AI-driven updates, manageable with prompting skills and team support.\
\
##### 1.4 Scheduling and Publishing\
- **Description**: Users schedule and automate video posts to social media.\
- **Key Features**:\
  - Platform selection (TikTok, YouTube Shorts), date/time picker, visibility options, frequency settings, "Schedule Post" button.\
- **Implementation Details**:\
  - Frontend: Calendar components, checkboxes for platforms, radio buttons for visibility, dropdowns for frequency.\
  - Backend: Integrates with TikTok/YouTube APIs for publishing, using OAuth, with workflow automation for scheduling.\
- **User Flow**: Users select platforms, set schedule, choose visibility/frequency, confirm, with the system handling automated posting (App Flow Document, Stage 5).\
- **Feasibility**: Bubble's workflow automation and Zapier integrations can handle scheduling, with team support for API setups.\
\
